dcterms:creator: Raj Singh
Evelina Fedorenko
Kyle Mahowald
Edward Gibson
dcterms:description: This dataset consists of human behavioral acceptance judgment experiments using presupposition triggers, where participants evaluate the sensibility of sentences based on the plausibility of the presupposed information.
dcterms:title: Singh et al. (2016) Presupposition Dataset

dcterms:creator: Mante S. Nieuwland
Tali Ditman
Gina R. Kuperberg
dcterms:description: This dataset includes items designed to investigate the incrementality of pragmatic processing, focusing on scalar implicatures and how they are processed in sentence comprehension.
dcterms:title: Nieuwland et al. (2010) Scalar Implicature Dataset

dcterms:creator: Paloma Jeretic
Alex Warstadt
Suvrat Bhooshan
Adina Williams
dcterms:description: The ImpPress dataset consists of semi-automatically generated sentence pairs that illustrate various commonsense pragmatic inference types, including presupposition and implicature.
dcterms:title: ImpPress Dataset
